SELECT 'b2000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','f16b79dc-50f8-4022-8de8-66bd15b8a529',NULL,'navigating-insurance-for-mental-health-care','Navigating Insurance for Mental Health Care: A Comprehensive Guide','A plain-language guide to insurance terms, how coverage works step by step, and affordable options for therapy.','<p>Mental health coverage has expanded significantly over the past decade, largely thanks to the Mental Health Parity and Addiction Equity Act, which requires insurers to cover mental health on par with physical health. Still, the system has a lot of moving parts. Here is a plain-language guide.</p><h2>Key terms you need to know</h2><ul><li><strong>Premium</strong> &mdash; your monthly payment to keep coverage active.</li><li><strong>Deductible</strong> &mdash; what you pay out of pocket before insurance starts sharing costs.</li><li><strong>Copay</strong> &mdash; a flat fee per session.</li><li><strong>Coinsurance</strong> &mdash; a percentage of the session cost you share after meeting your deductible.</li><li><strong>Out-of-pocket max</strong> &mdash; the most you will pay in a year; insurance then covers 100%.</li><li><strong>In-network</strong> &mdash; therapists contracted with your insurer, usually much cheaper.</li><li><strong>Out-of-network</strong> &mdash; therapists without a contract; partial reimbursement may apply.</li><li><strong>Superbill</strong> &mdash; an itemized receipt you submit for out-of-network reimbursement.</li></ul><h2>How it works, step by step</h2><p><strong>1. Check your benefits.</strong> Call member services (the number on your card) or use your insurer&rsquo;s portal. Ask about outpatient mental health benefits, your deductible, and whether a referral is required.</p><p><strong>2. Find an in-network therapist.</strong> Use your insurer&rsquo;s directory filtered by behavioral health, and call to confirm current participation.</p><p><strong>3. Confirm coverage before your first session.</strong> Ask the therapist&rsquo;s office to verify your benefits, session cost, deductible status, and any pre-authorization needs.</p><p><strong>4. Attend your session.</strong> Your therapist submits a claim with a diagnosis code&mdash;standard for insurance payment. Talk with them about any privacy concerns.</p><p><strong>5. Pay your portion and track your deductible.</strong> You&rsquo;ll get an Explanation of Benefits (EOB) showing what was charged, what insurance covered, and what you owe.</p><h2>Insurance accepted at Brazen Therapy</h2><p>We are in-network with Aetna, Blue Cross Blue Shield, Cigna/Evernorth, United/UMR, Tricare, Triwest, ChampVA, and Optum. We verify your benefits before your first session so costs are clear.</p><h2>What if we don&rsquo;t take your insurance?</h2><p><strong>Out-of-network reimbursement:</strong> PPO plans often cover out-of-network care. We provide a superbill; typical reimbursement runs 40&ndash;70%.</p><p><strong>HSA / FSA:</strong> Therapy is a qualified medical expense, so you can pay tax-free and effectively reduce costs by 20&ndash;35%.</p><p><strong>Sliding scale &amp; intern rates:</strong> We offer reduced-cost care through sliding-scale rates and supervised graduate interns at significantly reduced fees.</p><h2>Common questions</h2><p><strong>Will my employer know I&rsquo;m in therapy?</strong> Individual treatment details are protected under HIPAA. Paying out of pocket keeps records entirely private.</p><p><strong>Can I use insurance for online therapy?</strong> Yes&mdash;most major insurers now cover telehealth at in-person rates.</p><p><strong>What if my claim is denied?</strong> You can appeal. Denials are often administrative, and many appeals succeed with proper documentation.</p>','/images/blog/insurance-guide.jpg',TRUE,FALSE,FALSE,now(),'{}'::text[],0,0,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM blog_posts WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='navigating-insurance-for-mental-health-care')
  AND EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM pages WHERE id='f16b79dc-50f8-4022-8de8-66bd15b8a529');

